{"title_page": "Maciej P\u0142aza", "text_new": "{{Infobox writer\n| name = Maciej P\u0142aza\n| image = RK1907 MG 5682 Maciej P\u0142aza.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Maciej P\u0142aza, 2019\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|12|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Opinog\u00f3ra G\u00f3rna|Opinog\u00f3ra]], [[Poland]]\n| alma_mater = [[Maria Curie-Sk\u0142odowska University]] (UMCS)\n| residence = [[Pozna\u0144]]\n| occupation = Writer, translator\n| nationality = Polish\n| language = \n| period =\n| genre = \n| notableworks = ''Robinson in Bolech\u00f3w'' \n| awards = [[Ko\u015bcielski Award]] (2016)<br />[[Gdynia Literary Prize]] (2016)<br />[[Angelus Award]] (2018)\n| signature = \n}}\n'''Maciej P\u0142aza''' (born 16 December 1976, [[Opinog\u00f3ra G\u00f3rna|Opinog\u00f3ra]]) is a [[Poles|Polish]] writer, literary scholar and translator of [[English literature]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://culture.pl/pl/tworca/maciej-plaza |title=Maciej P\u0142aza |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nHe is a graduate of [[Maria Curie-Sk\u0142odowska University]] in [[Lublin]]. He is a laureate of the Literature in the World Award for his translation of [[H. P. Lovecraft]]'s collection of short stories ''The Dunwich Horror and Others''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://instytutksiazki.pl/wydarzenia,aktualnosci,29796,nagrody-literatury-na-swiecie.html |title=Nagrody Literatury Na \u015awiecie |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref> In 2016, he became the recipient of the [[Gdynia Literary Prize]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nagrodaliterackagdynia.pl/wydarzenie/znamy-laureat%C3%B3w-11-edycji-nagrody-literackiej-gdynia |title=Znamy laureat\u00f3w 11. edycji Nagrody Literackiej GDYNIA! |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref> as well as the [[Ko\u015bcielski Award]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://instytutksiazki.pl/wydarzenia,aktualnosci,35630,maciej-plaza-z-nagroda-im--koscielskich.html |title=Maciej P\u0142aza z Nagrod\u0105 im. Ko\u015bcielskich |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref> He was also nominated for Poland's top literary prize [[Nike Award]] for his collection of stories entitled ''Skoru\u0144''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://culture.pl/pl/artykul/nominacje-do-nagrody-nike-2016 |title=Nominacje do nagrody Nike 2016 |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref> In 2018, he won the [[Angelus Award]] for his novel ''Robinson in Bolech\u00f3w'' becoming the first Polish writer to do so.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://angelus.com.pl/2018/10/maciej-plaza-laureatem-angelusa-2018/ |title=Maciej P\u0142aza laureatem Angelusa 2018 |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.polskieradio.pl/7/173/Artykul/2203830,Literacki-Angelus-dla-Macieja-Plazy |title=Literacki Angelus dla Macieja P\u0142azy |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n===Novels===\n*''O poznaniu w tw\u00f3rczo\u015bci Stanis\u0142awa Lema'', Wydawnictwo Uniwersytetu Wroc\u0142awskiego, Wroc\u0142aw, 2006\n*''Skoru\u0144'', Wydawnictwo W.A.B., Warsaw, 2015\n*''Robinson w Bolechowie'', Wydawnictwo W.A.B., Warsaw, 2017\n\n===Translations===\n*[[Christos Tsiolkas]], ''Martwa Europa'', Replika, Pozna\u0144, 2010\n*[[Fredric Jameson]], ''Archeologie przysz\u0142o\u015bci: pragnienie zwane utopi\u0105 i inne fantazje naukowe'', Wydawnictwo Uniwersytetu Jagiello\u0144skiego, Krak\u00f3w, 2011 (co-author)\n*[[Fredric Jameson]], ''Postmodernizm czyli Logika kulturowa p\u00f3\u017anego kapitalizmu'', Wydawnictwo Uniwersytetu Jagiello\u0144skiego, Krak\u00f3w, 2011\n*[[Brian McHale]], ''Powie\u015b\u0107 postmodernistyczna'', Wydawnictwo Uniwersytetu Jagiello\u0144skiego, Krak\u00f3w, 2011\n*[[H.P. Lovecraft]], ''Zgroza w Dunwich i inne przera\u017caj\u0105ce opowie\u015bci'', Vesper, Pozna\u0144, 2012\n*[[H.P. Lovecraft]], ''Przysz\u0142a na Sarnath zag\u0142ada: opowie\u015bci niesamowite i fantastyczne'', Vesper, Czerwonak, 2016\n*[[Mary Shelley]], ''Frankenstein czyli Wsp\u00f3\u0142czesny Prometeusz'', Vesper, Czerwonak, 2013\n*[[Jenny Diski]], ''Lata sze\u015b\u0107dziesi\u0105te'', Officyna, \u0141\u00f3d\u017a, 2013\n*[[Kenneth Grahame]], ''O czym szumi\u0105 wierzby'', Vesper, Pozna\u0144, 2014\n*[[Mark Helprin]], ''Zimowa opowie\u015b\u0107'', Wydawnictwo Otwarte, Krak\u00f3w, 2014, (co-author)\n*[[Mark Helprin]], ''Pami\u0119tnik z mr\u00f3wkoszczelnej kasety'', Wydawnictwo Otwarte, Krak\u00f3w, 2014\n*[[Marjorie Perloff]], ''Ostrze ironii: modernizm w cieniu monarchii habsburskiej'', Ossolineum, Wroc\u0142aw, 2018\n*DeSales Harrison, ''Zostaw ten \u015bwiat pe\u0142en p\u0142aczu'', Marginesy, Warszawa, 2019\n\n==See also==\n*[[Polish literature]]\n*[[Silesius Poetry Award]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Polish writers]]\n[[Category:Polish translators]]\n[[Category:Maria Curie-Sk\u0142odowska University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer\n| name = Maciej P\u0142aza\n| image = RK1907 MG 5682 Maciej P\u0142aza.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Maciej P\u0142aza, 2019\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|12|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Opinog\u00f3ra G\u00f3rna|Opinog\u00f3ra]], [[Poland]]\n| alma_mater = [[Maria Curie-Sk\u0142odowska University]] (UMCS)\n| residence = [[Pozna\u0144]]\n| occupation = Writer, translator\n| nationality = Polish\n| language = \n| period =\n| genre = \n| notableworks = ''Robinson in Bolech\u00f3w'' \n| awards = [[Ko\u015bcielski Award]] (2016)<br />[[Gdynia Literary Prize]] (2016)<br />[[Angelus Award]] (2018)\n| signature = \n}}\n'''Maciej P\u0142aza''' (born 16 December 1976, [[Opinog\u00f3ra G\u00f3rna|Opinog\u00f3ra]]) is a [[Poles|Polish]] writer, literary scholar and translator of [[English literature]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://culture.pl/pl/tworca/maciej-plaza |title=Maciej P\u0142aza |access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nHe is a graduate of [[Maria Curie-Sk\u0142odowska University]] in [[Lublin]]. He is a laureate of the Literature in the Wor